title: rustdoc: stack overflow: rustdoc::clean::clean_qpath()

labels.name: I-crash
labels.description: Issue: The compiler crashes (SIGSEGV, SIGABRT, etc). Use I-ICE instead when the compiler panics.

labels.name: T-rustdoc
labels.description: Relevant to the rustdoc team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-test
labels.description: Call for participation: writing correctness tests

body:
I tried this code: `./src/test/ui/impl-trait/recursive-type-alias-impl-trait-declaration-too-subtle-2.rs` ```rust #![feature(type_alias_impl_trait)] type Foo = impl PartialEq<(Foo, i32)>; struct Bar; impl PartialEq<(Foo, i32)> for Bar { //~^ ERROR cannot implement trait on type alias impl trait fn eq(&self, _other: &(Foo, i32)) -> bool { true } } fn foo() -> Foo { Bar } fn main() {} ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustdoc 1.63.0-nightly (ca122c7eb 2022-06-13) binary: rustdoc commit-hash: ca122c7ebb3ab50149c9d3d24ddb59c252b32272 commit-date: 2022-06-13 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.63.0-nightly LLVM version: 14.0.5 ```
